fields: In humans the {{c1::maxillary}} incisors are larger than the {{c1::mandibular}} incisors.
Incisors are important in {{c1::esthetics}}, {{c1::mastication}}, and {{c1::phonetics::asking for functions}}.
In refrence to your permanent maxillary central incisors the {{c1::I-C}} > {{c1::M-D}} > {{c1::F-L}} in width.
Which tooth has the widest mesial to distal measurment of all anterior teeth? What is the M-D almost as wide as?
Maxillary central incisors. The Mesial-Distal width is almost as wide as the Incisal edge-CEJ width.
Describe the developmental timeline for maxillary central incisors: when is the beginning of calcification, completion of enamel, eruption, and root completion?

Beginning of calcification: 3-4 months
Completion of Enamel: 4-5 years 
Eruption: 7-8 years 
Root Completion: 10 years
The basic crown shape of a maxillary central incisor is a {{c1::trapezoid}}.
Compared to other incisors the {{c1::M-D}} and {{c1::I-C}} dimensions are nearly equal.
What is unique about the <u>facial cervical (CE) line</u> on maxillary central incisors?
The facial CE line curvature is more flat on maxillary central incisors than any other anterior teeth.
The incisal edge is {{c1::perpendicular}} to the long axis on maxillary central incisors.
Where are the height of contours (HOC's) on each surface of a maxillary central incisor?

Facial: cervical third
Lingual: cervical third 
Mesial: incisal third 
Distal: junction of incisal-middle third
The mamelons visible in newly erupted teeth occur: {{c1::MF}}, {{c1::MidF}}, {{c1::DF}} on a maxillary central incisor.
The mesial outiline is {{c1::straight}} while the distal outline is {{c1::more convex}} for a maxillary central incisor.

How to tell right from left lateral incisor: 

-{{c1::Mesio-incisal::MI/DI}} corner sharper than {{c1::Disto-incisal::MI/DI}} corner

-{{c1::Mesial::M/D}} cervical enamel line is {{c2::greater::greater/lesser}} than {{c1::distal::M/D}}

-{{c1::Mesial::M/D}} HOC more {{c2::incisal::cervical/medial/incisal}} than {{c1::distal::M/D}}

-{{c1::Distal::M/D}} outline more {{c2::convex::concave/convex}} 

-{{c2::Apex}} of root deflects {{c1::distally::mesially/distally}}
What are the two differences between the distal and medial views of the lateral incisors?

-HOC more cervical (closer to middle 1/3)
-CE line curvature less than mesial 


Slide 36
How does the incisal view of the lateral incisors differ from the central incisors?

More convex than central, creating a rounded triangular outline


Slide 37
How do the MD and FL dimensions of a lateral incisor compare?

MD is greater than or equal to FL dimensions 



Slide 37

The root of a lateral incisor is: 

-{{c1::single}} rooted

-wider {{c1::FL::MD/FL}} than {{c1::MD::MD/FL}}

-cross-section is more {{c1::ovoid::triangular/ovoid/circular}} than central incisor

-apical third may deflect {{c1::distally::distally/mesially}}
What's a peg tooth and which tooth tends to have this condition?

Lateral incisor that's not fully formed and conical in shape. May have congenital origin. 

Slide 39
How to tell if you have a maxillary lateral vs. central

-smaller in size than central except for root length

-distinct lingual anatomy (deeper lingual fossa, lingual pit)

-incisal, mesial, distal outlines are more rounded 


Slide 40
The DI angle is {{c1::more rounded}} than the MI angle of a maxillary central incisor.
The Mesial-Distal width is {{c1::slightly narrower}} on the lingual surface of a maxillary central incisor compared to the facial surface.
The lingual surface of a maxillary central incisor has {{c1::convexity}} and {{c1::concavity::talking about shape}}.
The CE curvature is greater on the {{c1::lingual surface}} compared to the {{c1::facial/labial surface}} of the maxillary central incisors.
The {{c1::mesial::surface}} CE curvature on the {{c2::maxillary central incisors::tooth type}} is greatest of any tooth.
When looking at a maxillary central incisor with a mesial view the facial outline is {{c1::slightly convex}} and the incisal 2/3 is {{c1::nearly flat.}}

When looking at a maxillary central incisor with a mesial view, the lingual outline is {{c1::S-Shape}}. The concave portion occurs {{c1::incisally::location}} and the convex portion occurs {{c1::cervically::location.}}
The incisal edge of a maxillary central incisor slopes {{c1::lingually}}.
The {{c1::distal}} CE line curvature is less than the {{c1::mesial}} CE line curvature in both maxillary central and lateral incisors.
The incisal edge is {{c1::midway}} faciolingually on a maxillary central incisor.
What are the characteristics of a maxiallary central incisor root? What shape is the cross section at the cervical end of the root? What is the ratio of crown to root?

Single root, concical, staight
At the cervical end of the root the cross-section is roughly triangular. 
2/5 Crown, 3/5 root

1. Smaller in all dimensions EXCEPT root length
2. generally more rounded
3. displays more variation in form
